text.tspan: In January 10, 2014, Vitalik put out a blueprint for a
new kind of economic democracy:
"it is possible to set up currencies whose seigniorage,
or issuance, goes to support certain causes, and
people can vote for those causes by accepting certain
currencies at their businesses. . ."
Fascinating. But what's a public good that's easy to
deliver and has well-understood benefits?
We have an answer:
. . . or the stopping of CO2 emissions. One ton of CO2
costs society $230 (according to the EPA), and we
have an easy way to stop millions of them.
In the Northeastern U.S., coal, oil, or gas power plants
must buy pollution rights to emit CO2.
Each year, states issue a fixed number of pollution rights—
enough for about 20% of France + Monaco’s total CO₂ emissions
(similar to the U.K.’s).
This matters because you can also buy pollution rights. Yes, you!
Power plants will use every last one to emit exactly one ton
of CO₂, unless you buy and permanently retire them first!
Ultra Civic lets you retire pollution rights in one click and
mints you 1 $PR (ERC-20 token) per retirement.
Stopping one ton of CO2 saves society $230 in damages and
costs you $24. That's your social impact, U.S. state-enforced.
